The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 October is 4,396 (508.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 October, there were 380 new confirmed cases (44.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 October, there were 331 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 15% ( 49 extra cases).
